      <div class="col-md-4">
        <h1> Buenos Aires </h1>

  <p>
  
    South America is largely unknown and unexplored in Midwestern education. Our popular conception of Latin America is so limited. We found Buenos Aires alive with people, with progressive culture and LGBT and trans pride around the city. So much of the youth culture reminds me of Athens or Seattle.

    Argentina presents another story of completely divergent lives, living right next to one another.
    
    A big difference, or perhaps just my ignorance, but we see so many families, full family units of moms, dads and two or more kids. They’re sleeping all together on the filthy street, and it strikes me what an individual plight it has always seemed to me, to be homeless. But a whole family homeless together felt different indeed.
    
    Of course there are kids on the street back home too, but it seems like a life circumstance that we largely view as occurring to a person, an individual.    
    
  </p>

      </div>
      <div class="col-md-8">

        
