      <div class="col-md-6">



        <h1> Crested caracara</h1>

  <p>
  
    Also, we found a Crested caracara sipping from Laguna Capri and edging around the proximity of beachgoers having lunch. This one was clearly habituated and didn’t seem to mind waltzing right up to me.

    In El Calafate we got wine and dessert at a literary themed restaurant in somewhat of a treehouse architecture with big windows overlooking the main street from the second story. The wifi password was “Borges.”
      
    The cab driver asks, what kind of music do you like? Who's your favorite band?
    
    We' "Uh, Metallica," she says.
    
    He leans forward, gives a couple taps of his phone, and proclaims, "Okay...Master of Puppets, here we go!" And we jet off toward the airport. He tells us how passionate he is for the football player Messi. In fact, the whole country has looped replays of the World Cup, which they had just won, playing on every pub TV. He takes a call from a stern faced boss, and chuckles, “Uh-oh.”
    
    “There are troubles,” he says, seeming to let it all roll off his shoulders. And then he takes a call from a young woman. “My queen,” he says. 
      
  
  </p>

  <img class="img-fluid rounded" src="https://summerlin.media/img/Condor.jpg" />

